{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Delighted to be here"},{"time":3000,"text":"and to talk to you about a subject dear to my heart,"},{"time":5000,"text":"which is beauty."},{"time":8000,"text":"I do the philosophy of art, aesthetics,"},{"time":11000,"text":"actually, for a living."},{"time":13000,"text":"I try to figure out intellectually,"},{"time":15000,"text":"philosophically, psychologically,"},{"time":17000,"text":"what the experience of beauty is,"},{"time":20000,"text":"what sensibly can be said about it"},{"time":23000,"text":"and how people go off the rails in trying to understand it."},{"time":26000,"text":"Now this is an extremely complicated subject,"},{"time":29000,"text":"in part because the things that we call beautiful"},{"time":32000,"text":"are so different."},{"time":34000,"text":"I mean just think of the sheer variety --"},{"time":36000,"text":"a baby's face,"},{"time":38000,"text":"Berlioz's \"Harold in Italy,\""},{"time":40000,"text":"movies like \"The Wizard of Oz\""},{"time":42000,"text":"or the plays of Chekhov,"},{"time":44000,"text":"a central California landscape,"},{"time":46000,"text":"a Hokusai view of Mt. Fuji,"},{"time":49000,"text":"\"Der Rosenkavalier,\""},{"time":51000,"text":"a stunning match-winning goal"},{"time":53000,"text":"in a World Cup soccer match,"},{"time":55000,"text":"Van Gogh's \"Starry Night,\""},{"time":57000,"text":"a Jane Austen novel,"},{"time":59000,"text":"Fred Astaire dancing across the screen."},{"time":62000,"text":"This brief list includes human beings,"},{"time":65000,"text":"natural landforms,"},{"time":67000,"text":"works of art and skilled human actions."},{"time":70000,"text":"An account that explains the presence of beauty"},{"time":73000,"text":"in everything on this list"},{"time":75000,"text":"is not going to be easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"I can, however, give you at least a taste"},{"time":80000,"text":"of what I regard"},{"time":82000,"text":"as the most powerful theory of beauty"},{"time":84000,"text":"we yet have."},{"time":86000,"text":"And we get it not from a philosopher of art,"},{"time":88000,"text":"not from a postmodern art theorist"},{"time":90000,"text":"or a bigwig art critic."},{"time":92000,"text":"No, this theory"},{"time":94000,"text":"comes from an expert"},{"time":96000,"text":"on barnacles and worms and pigeon breeding,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and you know who I mean:"},{"time":105000,"text":"Charles Darwin."},{"time":107000,"text":"Of course, a lot of people think they already know"},{"time":110000,"text":"the proper answer to the question,"},{"time":113000,"text":"\"What is beauty?\""},{"time":116000,"text":"It's in the eye of the beholder."},{"time":118000,"text":"It's whatever moves you personally."},{"time":120000,"text":"Or, as some people,"},{"time":122000,"text":"especially academics prefer,"},{"time":124000,"text":"beauty is in the culturally conditioned"},{"time":127000,"text":"eye of the beholder."},{"time":129000,"text":"People agree that paintings or movies or music"},{"time":132000,"text":"are beautiful"},{"time":134000,"text":"because their cultures determine a uniformity of aesthetic taste."},{"time":138000,"text":"Taste for both natural beauty and for the arts"},{"time":141000,"text":"travel across cultures"},{"time":143000,"text":"with great ease."},{"time":145000,"text":"Beethoven is adored in Japan."},{"time":147000,"text":"Peruvians love Japanese woodblock prints."},{"time":150000,"text":"Inca sculptures are regarded as treasures"},{"time":152000,"text":"in British museums,"},{"time":154000,"text":"while Shakespeare is translated"},{"time":156000,"text":"into every major language of the Earth."},{"time":159000,"text":"Or just think about American jazz"},{"time":161000,"text":"or American movies --"},{"time":163000,"text":"they go everywhere."},{"time":165000,"text":"There are many differences among the arts,"},{"time":168000,"text":"but there are also universal,"},{"time":170000,"text":"cross-cultural aesthetic pleasures"},{"time":172000,"text":"and values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"How can we explain"},{"time":177000,"text":"this universality?"},{"time":180000,"text":"The best answer lies in trying to reconstruct"},{"time":182000,"text":"a Darwinian evolutionary history"},{"time":185000,"text":"of our artistic and aesthetic tastes."},{"time":188000,"text":"We need to reverse-engineer"},{"time":190000,"text":"our present artistic tastes and preferences"},{"time":193000,"text":"and explain how they came"},{"time":195000,"text":"to be engraved in our minds"},{"time":198000,"text":"by the actions of both our prehistoric,"},{"time":201000,"text":"largely pleistocene environments,"},{"time":203000,"text":"where we became fully human,"},{"time":205000,"text":"but also by the social situations"},{"time":207000,"text":"in which we evolved."},{"time":209000,"text":"This reverse engineering"},{"time":211000,"text":"can also enlist help"},{"time":214000,"text":"from the human record"},{"time":216000,"text":"preserved in prehistory."},{"time":218000,"text":"I mean fossils, cave paintings and so forth."},{"time":221000,"text":"And it should take into account"},{"time":223000,"text":"what we know of the aesthetic interests"},{"time":225000,"text":"of isolated hunter-gatherer bands"},{"time":228000,"text":"that survived into the 19th and the 20th centuries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"Now, I personally"},{"time":234000,"text":"have no doubt whatsoever"},{"time":236000,"text":"that the experience of beauty,"},{"time":238000,"text":"with its emotional intensity and pleasure,"},{"time":241000,"text":"belongs to our evolved human psychology."},{"time":245000,"text":"The experience of beauty is one component"},{"time":248000,"text":"in a whole series of Darwinian adaptations."},{"time":252000,"text":"Beauty is an adaptive effect,"},{"time":254000,"text":"which we extend"},{"time":256000,"text":"and intensify"},{"time":258000,"text":"in the creation and enjoyment"},{"time":260000,"text":"of works of art and entertainment."},{"time":264000,"text":"As many of you will know,"},{"time":266000,"text":"evolution operates by two main primary mechanisms."},{"time":269000,"text":"The first of these is natural selection --"},{"time":272000,"text":"that's random mutation and selective retention --"},{"time":275000,"text":"along with our basic anatomy and physiology --"},{"time":278000,"text":"the evolution of the pancreas or the eye or the fingernails."},{"time":281000,"text":"Natural selection also explains"},{"time":284000,"text":"many basic revulsions,"},{"time":286000,"text":"such as the horrid smell of rotting meat,"},{"time":288000,"text":"or fears, such as the fear of snakes"},{"time":291000,"text":"or standing close to the edge of a cliff."},{"time":294000,"text":"Natural selection also explains pleasures --"},{"time":297000,"text":"sexual pleasure,"},{"time":299000,"text":"our liking for sweet, fat and proteins,"},{"time":302000,"text":"which in turn explains a lot of popular foods,"},{"time":305000,"text":"from ripe fruits through chocolate malts"},{"time":308000,"text":"and barbecued ribs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"The other great principle of evolution"},{"time":313000,"text":"is sexual selection,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and it operates very differently."},{"time":317000,"text":"The peacock's magnificent tail"},{"time":320000,"text":"is the most famous example of this."},{"time":323000,"text":"It did not evolve for natural survival."},{"time":326000,"text":"In fact, it goes against natural survival."},{"time":329000,"text":"No, the peacock's tail"},{"time":331000,"text":"results from the mating choices"},{"time":333000,"text":"made by peahens."},{"time":335000,"text":"It's quite a familiar story."},{"time":337000,"text":"It's women who actually push history forward."},{"time":341000,"text":"Darwin himself, by the way,"},{"time":343000,"text":"had no doubts that the peacock's tail"},{"time":345000,"text":"was beautiful in the eyes of the peahen."},{"time":347000,"text":"He actually used that word."},{"time":350000,"text":"Now, keeping these ideas firmly in mind,"},{"time":353000,"text":"we can say that the experience of beauty"},{"time":356000,"text":"is one of the ways that evolution has"},{"time":359000,"text":"of arousing and sustaining"},{"time":361000,"text":"interest or fascination,"},{"time":363000,"text":"even obsession,"},{"time":365000,"text":"in order to encourage us"},{"time":367000,"text":"toward making the most adaptive decisions"},{"time":370000,"text":"for survival and reproduction."},{"time":374000,"text":"Beauty is nature's way"},{"time":376000,"text":"of acting at a distance,"},{"time":379000,"text":"so to speak."},{"time":381000,"text":"I mean, you can't expect to eat"},{"time":383000,"text":"an adaptively beneficial landscape."},{"time":385000,"text":"It would hardly do to eat your baby"},{"time":387000,"text":"or your lover."},{"time":389000,"text":"So evolution's trick"},{"time":391000,"text":"is to make them beautiful,"},{"time":393000,"text":"to have them exert a kind of magnetism"},{"time":396000,"text":"to give you the pleasure of simply looking at them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400000,"text":"Consider briefly an important source of aesthetic pleasure,"},{"time":403000,"text":"the magnetic pull"},{"time":405000,"text":"of beautiful landscapes."},{"time":407000,"text":"People in very different cultures"},{"time":409000,"text":"all over the world"},{"time":411000,"text":"tend to like a particular kind of landscape,"},{"time":414000,"text":"a landscape that just happens to be similar"},{"time":417000,"text":"to the pleistocene savannas where we evolved."},{"time":420000,"text":"This landscape shows up today"},{"time":422000,"text":"on calendars, on postcards,"},{"time":425000,"text":"in the design of golf courses and public parks"},{"time":428000,"text":"and in gold-framed pictures"},{"time":430000,"text":"that hang in living rooms"},{"time":432000,"text":"from New York to New Zealand."},{"time":435000,"text":"It's a kind of Hudson River school landscape"},{"time":438000,"text":"featuring open spaces"},{"time":440000,"text":"of low grasses"},{"time":442000,"text":"interspersed with copses of trees."},{"time":445000,"text":"The trees, by the way, are often preferred"},{"time":447000,"text":"if they fork near the ground,"},{"time":449000,"text":"that is to say, if they're trees you could scramble up"},{"time":452000,"text":"if you were in a tight fix."},{"time":455000,"text":"The landscape shows the presence"},{"time":457000,"text":"of water directly in view,"},{"time":459000,"text":"or evidence of water in a bluish distance,"},{"time":463000,"text":"indications of animal or bird life"},{"time":466000,"text":"as well as diverse greenery"},{"time":468000,"text":"and finally -- get this --"},{"time":471000,"text":"a path"},{"time":473000,"text":"or a road,"},{"time":475000,"text":"perhaps a riverbank or a shoreline,"},{"time":478000,"text":"that extends into the distance,"},{"time":481000,"text":"almost inviting you to follow it."},{"time":485000,"text":"This landscape type is regarded as beautiful,"},{"time":488000,"text":"even by people in countries"},{"time":490000,"text":"that don't have it."},{"time":492000,"text":"The ideal savanna landscape"},{"time":494000,"text":"is one of the clearest examples"},{"time":496000,"text":"where human beings everywhere"},{"time":498000,"text":"find beauty"},{"time":500000,"text":"in similar visual experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502000,"text":"But, someone might argue,"},{"time":504000,"text":"that's natural beauty."},{"time":506000,"text":"How about artistic beauty?"},{"time":509000,"text":"Isn't that exhaustively cultural?"},{"time":512000,"text":"No, I don't think it is."},{"time":514000,"text":"And once again, I'd like to look back to prehistory"},{"time":517000,"text":"to say something about it."},{"time":519000,"text":"It is widely assumed"},{"time":521000,"text":"that the earliest human artworks"},{"time":523000,"text":"are the stupendously skillful cave paintings"},{"time":526000,"text":"that we all know from Lascaux"},{"time":528000,"text":"and Chauvet."},{"time":531000,"text":"Chauvet caves"},{"time":533000,"text":"are about 32,000 years old,"},{"time":535000,"text":"along with a few small, realistic sculptures"},{"time":538000,"text":"of women and animals from the same period."},{"time":545000,"text":"But artistic and decorative skills"},{"time":547000,"text":"are actually much older than that."},{"time":551000,"text":"Beautiful shell necklaces"},{"time":553000,"text":"that look like something you'd see at an arts and crafts fair,"},{"time":556000,"text":"as well as ochre body paint,"},{"time":558000,"text":"have been found"},{"time":560000,"text":"from around 100,000 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"But the most intriguing prehistoric artifacts"},{"time":565000,"text":"are older even than this."},{"time":567000,"text":"I have in mind"},{"time":569000,"text":"the so-called Acheulian hand axes."},{"time":573000,"text":"The oldest stone tools are choppers"},{"time":576000,"text":"from the Olduvai Gorge in East Africa."},{"time":578000,"text":"They go back about two-and-a-half-million years."},{"time":581000,"text":"These crude tools"},{"time":583000,"text":"were around for thousands of centuries,"},{"time":586000,"text":"until around 1.4 million years ago"},{"time":589000,"text":"when Homo erectus"},{"time":591000,"text":"started shaping"},{"time":593000,"text":"single, thin stone blades,"},{"time":595000,"text":"sometimes rounded ovals,"},{"time":598000,"text":"but often in what are to our eyes"},{"time":600000,"text":"an arresting, symmetrical pointed leaf"},{"time":603000,"text":"or teardrop form."},{"time":605000,"text":"These Acheulian hand axes --"},{"time":607000,"text":"they're named after St. Acheul in France,"},{"time":609000,"text":"where finds were made in 19th century --"},{"time":612000,"text":"have been unearthed in their thousands,"},{"time":615000,"text":"scattered across Asia, Europe and Africa,"},{"time":618000,"text":"almost everywhere Homo erectus"},{"time":621000,"text":"and Homo ergaster roamed."},{"time":624000,"text":"Now, the sheer numbers of these hand axes"},{"time":627000,"text":"shows that they can't have been made"},{"time":629000,"text":"for butchering animals."},{"time":631000,"text":"And the plot really thickens when you realize"},{"time":634000,"text":"that, unlike other pleistocene tools,"},{"time":637000,"text":"the hand axes often exhibit"},{"time":639000,"text":"no evidence of wear"},{"time":641000,"text":"on their delicate blade edges."},{"time":643000,"text":"And some, in any event, are too big"},{"time":645000,"text":"to use for butchery."},{"time":648000,"text":"Their symmetry, their attractive materials"},{"time":650000,"text":"and, above all,"},{"time":652000,"text":"their meticulous workmanship"},{"time":654000,"text":"are simply quite beautiful"},{"time":657000,"text":"to our eyes, even today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660000,"text":"So what were these ancient --"},{"time":664000,"text":"I mean, they're ancient, they're foreign,"},{"time":666000,"text":"but they're at the same time"},{"time":668000,"text":"somehow familiar."},{"time":670000,"text":"What were these artifacts for?"},{"time":673000,"text":"The best available answer"},{"time":675000,"text":"is that they were literally"},{"time":677000,"text":"the earliest known works of art,"},{"time":679000,"text":"practical tools transformed"},{"time":681000,"text":"into captivating aesthetic objects,"},{"time":684000,"text":"contemplated both for their elegant shape"},{"time":686000,"text":"and their virtuoso craftsmanship."},{"time":690000,"text":"Hand axes mark"},{"time":692000,"text":"an evolutionary advance in human history --"},{"time":694000,"text":"tools fashioned to function"},{"time":696000,"text":"as what Darwinians call \"fitness signals\" --"},{"time":699000,"text":"that is to say, displays"},{"time":701000,"text":"that are performances"},{"time":703000,"text":"like the peacock's tail,"},{"time":705000,"text":"except that, unlike hair and feathers,"},{"time":708000,"text":"the hand axes are consciously"},{"time":710000,"text":"cleverly crafted."},{"time":712000,"text":"Competently made hand axes"},{"time":714000,"text":"indicated desirable personal qualities --"},{"time":718000,"text":"intelligence, fine motor control,"},{"time":721000,"text":"planning ability,"},{"time":723000,"text":"conscientiousness"},{"time":725000,"text":"and sometimes access to rare materials."},{"time":728000,"text":"Over tens of thousands of generations,"},{"time":731000,"text":"such skills increased the status"},{"time":733000,"text":"of those who displayed them"},{"time":735000,"text":"and gained a reproductive advantage"},{"time":737000,"text":"over the less capable."},{"time":739000,"text":"You know, it's an old line,"},{"time":741000,"text":"but it has been shown to work --"},{"time":743000,"text":"\"Why don't you come up to my cave, so I can show you my hand axes?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"Except, of course, what's interesting about this"},{"time":751000,"text":"is that we can't be sure how that idea was conveyed,"},{"time":754000,"text":"because the Homo erectus"},{"time":756000,"text":"that made these objects"},{"time":759000,"text":"did not have language."},{"time":761000,"text":"It's hard to grasp,"},{"time":763000,"text":"but it's an incredible fact."},{"time":766000,"text":"This object was made"},{"time":768000,"text":"by a hominid ancestor,"},{"time":771000,"text":"Homo erectus or Homo ergaster,"},{"time":775000,"text":"between 50,000 and 100,000 years"},{"time":778000,"text":"before language."},{"time":781000,"text":"Stretching over a million years,"},{"time":783000,"text":"the hand axe tradition"},{"time":785000,"text":"is the longest artistic tradition"},{"time":788000,"text":"in human and proto-human history."},{"time":791000,"text":"By the end of the hand axe epic, Homo sapiens --"},{"time":794000,"text":"as they were then called, finally --"},{"time":796000,"text":"were doubtless finding new ways"},{"time":798000,"text":"to amuse and amaze each other"},{"time":801000,"text":"by, who knows, telling jokes,"},{"time":803000,"text":"storytelling, dancing, or hairstyling."},{"time":806000,"text":"Yes, hairstyling -- I insist on that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"For us moderns,"},{"time":811000,"text":"virtuoso technique"},{"time":813000,"text":"is used to create imaginary worlds"},{"time":815000,"text":"in fiction and in movies,"},{"time":817000,"text":"to express intense emotions"},{"time":819000,"text":"with music, painting and dance."},{"time":822000,"text":"But still,"},{"time":824000,"text":"one fundamental trait"},{"time":826000,"text":"of the ancestral personality persists"},{"time":828000,"text":"in our aesthetic cravings:"},{"time":831000,"text":"the beauty we find"},{"time":833000,"text":"in skilled performances."},{"time":835000,"text":"From Lascaux to the Louvre"},{"time":837000,"text":"to Carnegie Hall,"},{"time":839000,"text":"human beings"},{"time":841000,"text":"have a permanent innate taste"},{"time":843000,"text":"for virtuoso displays in the arts."},{"time":847000,"text":"We find beauty"},{"time":849000,"text":"in something done well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"So the next time you pass a jewelry shop window"},{"time":855000,"text":"displaying a beautifully cut"},{"time":857000,"text":"teardrop-shaped stone,"},{"time":859000,"text":"don't be so sure"},{"time":861000,"text":"it's just your culture telling you"},{"time":863000,"text":"that that sparkling jewel is beautiful."},{"time":865000,"text":"Your distant ancestors loved that shape"},{"time":868000,"text":"and found beauty in the skill needed to make it,"},{"time":871000,"text":"even before"},{"time":873000,"text":"they could put their love into words."},{"time":875000,"text":"Is beauty in the eye of the beholder?"},{"time":878000,"text":"No, it's deep in our minds."},{"time":881000,"text":"It's a gift handed down from the intelligent skills"},{"time":884000,"text":"and rich emotional lives"},{"time":886000,"text":"of our most ancient ancestors."},{"time":889000,"text":"Our powerful reaction to images,"},{"time":891000,"text":"to the expression of emotion in art,"},{"time":894000,"text":"to the beauty of music, to the night sky,"},{"time":897000,"text":"will be with us and our descendants"},{"time":900000,"text":"for as long as the human race exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}